      <p>
        <code>flex-basis</code> defines the default size of a flex item before the extra space is distributed.
        <br>
        It can assume a length (like 20% or 20em, px, etc) or a keyword. The available keywords are:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>auto: which is the default value.</li>
        <li>content</li>
        <li>fill</li>
        <li>max-content</li>
        <li>min-content</li>
        <li>fit-content</li>
      </ul>
      <p>None of these values (except for the “auto”), are well supported yet, what makes it hard to test and to understand.</p>
